        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add session stream mode command",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds a shared `/stream` command (alias `/streaming`) for session-scoped preview streaming mode overrides without editing channel config or restarting the gateway.\n- Persists the canonical mode on `SessionEntry.streamingMode`; accepted modes are `off`, `partial`, `block`, and `progress`. The command accepts `final` as a user-facing alias for canonical `off`.\n- Extends the shared preview streaming resolver so session mode wins before channel/account config and default mode.\n- Wires the override through Telegram, Discord, and Slack dispatch paths, and adds an explicit channel capability so unsupported channels refuse the command instead of falsely acknowledging a setting they will ignore.\n- Intentionally out of scope: `/progress` / `streaming.preview.toolProgress` from #80989, Mattermost/MS Teams/Matrix runtime wiring, and protocol/TUI patch support.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #74077\n\nRelated #80989\nRelated #81009\n\nRequested by the open issue and shaped by the prior #81009 failure mode: shared commands must either be honored everywhere they are accepted or explicitly refuse on unsupported surfaces.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior addressed: `/stream` / `/streaming` can set a per-session preview streaming override for capable channels, the shared resolver uses the session override before channel config, and incapable channels do not persist a fake override.\n- Real environment tested: local OpenClaw source checkout on Linux, branch `clawsean/stream-mode-session-command`, rebased onto current `upstream/main` (`caab343461`).\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: `node --import tsx --input-type=module` with production `src/auto-reply/reply/commands-session.ts` and `src/plugin-sdk/channel-streaming.ts` imports; targeted Vitest; `pnpm tsgo:prod`; `pnpm check:test-types`; `git diff --check`.\n- Evidence after fix: terminal capture from the production resolver/handler smoke:\n\n```console\n$ node --import tsx --input-type=module\n{\n  \"unsupportedReply\": \"⚙️ /stream isn't supported on this channel yet.\",\n  \"unsupportedStoredMode\": null,\n  \"resolverSessionMode\": \"progress\",\n  \"resolverWithoutSessionMode\": \"partial\"\n}\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: unsupported channel handling refused `/stream` without writing `SessionEntry.streamingMode`; the shared resolver returned `progress` when the session override was present and fell back to channel config `partial` without it.\n- What was not tested: live Telegram, Discord, or Slack UI behavior from a deployed gateway branch; Mattermost/MS Teams/Matrix are intentionally unsupported by the new capability gate in this PR.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: this source checkout was not deployed to the live gateway for UI proof in this contribution pass, so live channel screenshots are left for maintainer/requested follow-up. Local runtime/unit coverage covers command registration, set/status/reset, unsupported-channel refusal/no persist, resolver session precedence, and Telegram/Discord/Slack helper precedence.\n- Before evidence: current `main` has no `/stream` command/session override; prior related PR #81009 demonstrated the failure mode where a shared command acknowledged an override only one channel honored.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugin-sdk/channel-streaming.test.ts src/auto-reply/commands-registry.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-session-usage.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/preview-streaming.test.ts extensions/discord/src/preview-streaming.test.ts extensions/slack/src/stream-mode.test.ts` — passed, 5 shards / 88 tests.\n- `pnpm tsgo:prod`.\n- `pnpm check:test-types`.\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD` and `git diff --check` — passed.\n- Earlier `node scripts/check.mjs --timed` on the first branch head was blocked by stale `npm-shrinkwrap.json` guard before later gates; this PR does not change dependencies.\n- Earlier local `check-changed` child path on the first branch head passed core prod typecheck, then hit existing `packages/gateway-protocol/src/native-protocol-levels.guard.test.ts` type errors. `pnpm check:test-types` now passes locally on the current base.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? `Yes`\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? `No`\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? `No`\n\nHighest-risk area: shared command exposure vs channel runtime honoring, the same class of issue that closed #81009.\n\nMitigation: this PR introduces `previewStreamingSessionOverride` as an explicit channel capability, marks only Telegram/Discord/Slack as capable, and gates `handleStreamCommand` so unsupported channels reply that `/stream` is unsupported and do not persist an override.\n\n## Current review state\n\n- Author implementation complete and pushed as one commit.\n- Awaiting maintainer/ClawSweeper review on the session override storage shape, the capability gate, and whether Telegram/Discord/Slack is the right MVP channel set.\n- Known caveat: live UI proof is not included yet; local runtime/unit coverage and a runtime resolver/handler smoke transcript are included.\n",
